#Text=DS : Do you think it ’s hurt the peace process , the Lebanese War ?
#Text=SP : I do n’t think so .
#Text=You know what is promoting the peace prospect more than losing it ?
#Text=That no one in the Middle East wants to fall under the spell of Iran .
#Text=Iran today is a country with an appetite .
#Text=An imperial appetite .
#Text=They want an Iranian hegemony in the Middle East in the name of god and enriched uranium .
#Text=And nobody wants it .
#Text=So they attended Annapolis for the same reason .
#Text=So everything , you know , it ’s not a one-sided situation .
#Text=It ’s very dialectical , including Iran .
#Text=So they think they won .
#Text=What did they win ?
#Text=They are less accused ; they are not less watched , not less disliked and not less suspected .
#Text=DS : Do you think there is still a strong peace movement in Israel ?
#Text=SP : I think the situation is a peace movement because the more that the Arabs are learning , the more they are becoming peaceful .
#Text=Look , we have in Israel 50,000 Arab citizens who are academicians .
#Text=Ask where are they .
#Text=Some of them are teachers who will remain in the vicinity of their university .
#Text=Most of them are doctors .
#Text=You wo n’t find in Israel today a hospital without Arab doctors and Arab nurses .

#Text=Now an Israeli that goes to the hospital , maybe he would be reluctant to employ an Arab at his factory but he does n’t hesitate to come to the hospital , lie on the bed and here comes an Arab doctor with a knife in his hand and operates on him .
#Text=And he says thank you .
#Text=So if you have healthy relations in hospitals , maybe it ’s a cure for the others .
#Text=The more people who become professional and modern from both sides , this is the peace movement !
#Text=The peace movement is not an attempt to write more songs about peace .
#Text=We have enough songs .
#Text=What we need is the development and we have to be passionate .
#Text=On American politics
#Text=DS :
#Text=How have you seen America ’s role in the peace process change between Clinton to Bush ?
#Text=SP : Look at America after the elections .
#Text=In my journal , the two parties will come together and try to work up a bipartisan policy .
#Text=You know somebody said that the difference between the Republicans and Democrats is the Democrats are reformers and the Republicans are maintainers .
#Text=So they put in a little bit the Democrats to reform , then they put in the Republican to maintain .

#Text=Then they change , but they keep basic on foreign affairs ; America is revolutionary in technology , in economy , but very balanced in foreign policy and even when the United States commits mistakes in her foreign policy , a foreign policy without America would be the greatest mistake of our generation .
